<br>
I know people get hired all the time by contacts (I am assured a teaching job here through contacts), but they must fly the job before they can even interview.  They have to accept applications from others, and do the interview process.  They can't interview before the postition is flown... a whole bunch of things.  It's in the unfair hiring practice clause in some law somewhere.<br>
<br>
Every job I will get call to interview for here has been &quot;flown&quot;.  If they don't fly it, the can't hire for it.<br>
<br>
I guess I'm off to call my lawyer. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START  >D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/grin.gif ALT=" >D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
